        [
          "You were a proud, bra-burning feminist in the 1960s, but you also thought the way to affect social change was through intelligent discourse.  When the police beat you for being part of a protest march, you started to reconsider your views on violence.  While you were recovering, you were approached by a woman who said that she knew a group that could help you channel your new found anger, and she gave you a number to call.  It took you a few months, but you did do it.  The group didn't have a name, but it was full of strange and wonderful women who took no shit.  You were frankly a bit intimidated by them at first, but you eventually settled into the feel of things.  After your embrace, you realized that you had been being groomed to take your place as one of the Dark Mother's Priestesses.  Your embrace was not an event that you recall fondly, but you gained new enlightenment into the gifts of pain.  Your pack believes you to be on Path of Night, and when the Inquisition came knocking, you convinced *them* that you just need to be pushed back on to the right variant of that. But you also know they're still watching.  Just because your time in their hands was educational, it doesn't mean that you wish to go back."
